I'm new to HubSpot and trying to create a quote in a workflow. I understand this is only possible using "custom code" so I have created this custom code in a workflow and I have 2 issues.
*First an authentication 401 error* 
```const HubSpot = require('@HubSpot/api-client');
const DEAL_STAGE_ID = 'appointmentscheduled';
const PIPELINE_ID = 'default';
const QUOTE_TEMPLATE_ID = 'MODERN'

exports.main = async (event, callback) =&gt; {
  const dealName = event.inputFields['dealName'];
  const ownerID = event.inputFields['HubSpot_owner_id'];
  const companyId = event.inputFields['company_id']
  try {
  const HubSpotClient = new HubSpot.Client({
    accessToken: 'CJKbnf.....'
  });

  const results = await HubSpotClient.crm.deals.basicApi.getById(event.object.objectId)
  let objectId = results.properties.hs_object_id
  let contract_length = results.properties.contract_length;
  let amount = results.properties.amount;
  let closedate = results.properties.closedate;

  const newQuote = await HubSpotClient.crm.quotes.basicApi.create({
    properties: {
    	hs_title: dealName,
  		hs_expiration_date: "2023-08-30",
  		HubSpot_owner_id: ownerID,
      	hs_status: "APPROVAL_NOT_NEEDED",
        hs_language: "en",
        hs_sender_email: "<mailto:email@domain.com|email@domain.com>",
        hs_template: QUOTE_TEMPLATE_ID,
        hs_template_type: "CUSTOMIZABLE_QUOTE_TEMPLATE",
        hs_slug: "some_slug",
        hs_domain: "USER_DEFINED",
        hs_currency: "USD",    
    }
  })
  const quoteID = newQuote.id

callback({
    outputFields: {
      quoteID: quoteID
    }
  })
    } catch(error) {
    console.log(error.body || error)
  }
}```
I have created a Private App and all that, but how do I get authenticated in an automated way through "custom code", do I need to create my own server to handle that? if so how should I call my server and handle the authentication from custom code?

